# How to start docker
=====================

On mac first start the virtual machine that runs docker by running

```boot2docker up```

Default password is tcuser

Then log in to the virtual machine with ssh:

```boot2docker ssh```

In another terminal, find out which ip your boot2docker is running on:

```boot2docker ip```

Upload the Dockerfile with scp:

```scp Dockerfile docker@ip:~/Dockerfiles/concoct```


Upload the test data:

```scp ~/repos/CONCOCT-test-data/reads 

In the first terminal window, build the docker image:

```cd ~/Dockerfiles/concoct/
   docker build -t binpro/concoct_cami```


And then run the docker container:

```docker run -v /data/location/cami/input:/dckr/mnt/input:ro \
    -v /data/location/cami/output:/dckr/mnt/output:rw default```
